                section#safety-plan
                    h3 CCST Vancouver – COVID-19 Safety Plan
                    div In compliance with the orders or guidance issued by the Provincial Health Officer and the COVID-19 Go-Forward Guidelines produced by B.C. Post-Secondary Institutions with the support of the Ministry of Advanced Education, Skills and Training, we have prepared the COVID-19 Safety Plan at CCST Vancouver. We would like to provide a safe and healthy environment for the community of CCST Vancouver. 
                    ul
                        li.pb-15
                            div Daily Operation
                            ul
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    div Ensure that anyone showing symptoms of COVID-19 is prohibited from entering CCST Vancouver.
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Anyone who has symptoms of COVID-19 in the last 14 days.  Symptoms include fever, chills, new or worsening cough, shortness of breath, sore throat, and new muscle aches or headache.
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Anyone under the direction of public health to self-isolate must follow those instructions as well.
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Anyone who has arrived from outside of Canada or who has contacted with a confirmed COVID-19 case must self-isolate for 14 days and monitor for symptoms.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Staffs, students and visitors should sign in every time when arriving campus.  The administrator keeps the sign in record till the end of the Pandemic.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Staffs, students and visitors should check their temperature at the entrance of the building.  All people with a 37C temperature will be prohibited on the campus.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Students and visitors should wear a mask in the campus premises. Masks are provided for those who do not have their own.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Follow the signage of occupancy limits in all common areas.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Maintain a distance of 2 meters (6 feet) with one another between staff, students and others wherever possible.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    div Ensure handwashing is an important part of maintaining a healthy environment.
                                    div Please wash your hands: 
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') When arriving at the campus
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Before and after going for a break (especially if using common break rooms)
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Periodically throughout the day, especially if interfacing with people
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') After handling delivery documents, packages, boxes and bags
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') As you leave the school building
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    div Look for alternative communications
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Whenever possible, choose to communicate by phone, email, etc.  
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Consider work from home arrangements.
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Avoid meetings or gatherings where physical distance cannot be maintained. Consider using larger rooms, moving meetings to larger areas, or having all or some attendees attend virtually.
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Where possible, cancel in-person meetings and hold meetings by teleconference, video conference, or email instead.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    div During the pandemic, we should limit visitors outside the CCST Vancouver Community  
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') meet visitors by appointment 
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') keep record of all visitors
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') avoid offering food and beverages 
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') a no-touch thermometer is available by the side of the front door for check in  
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    div If someone begins to feel ill while at campus and display possible COVID-19 symptoms:
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') Report to any administrator that you are concerned about the spread of COVID-19 in the workplace and you believe that an individual is displaying symptoms.
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') The administrator should quickly isolate the individual; briefly ask who they have been working closely with, in which areas of the workplace and with which equipment; then send them home immediately. The administrator will then send any identified close contacts home. The administrator should clean and disinfect areas where the individual was working and any equipment or tools used.                                
                                        li(style='list-style:disc') 
                                            span Any worker who exhibits possible symptoms of COVID-19 and has sent home will need to follow the self-isolation guidance contained within the online BC COVID-19 Symptom Self-Assessment Tool.  
                                            a(href='https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en' target='_blank') https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span Any worker who exhibits possible symptoms of COVID-19 and has sent home will need to follow the self-isolation guidance contained within the online BC COVID-19 Symptom Self-Assessment Tool.  
                                    a(href="https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en" target="_blank") https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en

                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    div Ensure disinfection is an important part of maintaining a safe environment.  The administrative team disinfects the common areas: 
                                    ul
                                        li Before and after someone using an area
                                        li Periodically throughout the day, especially during the “open to the public” hours
                                        li At the end of the day
                                        li Shared tools and equipment are limited
                                        li 
                                            span Cleaning and disinfect procedures should be done according to this link 
                                            a(href='http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/CleaningDisinfecting_PublicSettings.pdf' target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/CleaningDisinfecting_PublicSettings.pdf
                                
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Limit ”Work at the Office Days” from Tuesday to Thursday ONLY.

                                li(style='list-style:decimal') All full-time staff are briefed with all CCST Vancouver COVID-19 Safety Plan documents.  A copy of the CCST Vancouver COVID-19 Plan is available in the library as well.
                        
                        li.pb-15    
                            div Class Arrangement
                            ul 
                                li We change our teaching format in order to accommodate the B.C. Post-Secondary COVID-19 Go-Forward Guideline, which include using online teaching format whenever possible.  And we stop all on-site teaching or blended class since the new restrictions announced on November 25, 2020.  We will keep using the online format till the end of the pandemic.
                        
                        li.pb-15
                            div Library
                            ul
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') There is limited occupancy for the CCST Vancouver Library.  The library staff and all other staff are responsible to implement measures to restrict the number of people in the library at one time.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Encourage teachers and students to make appointment to use the library resources in order to restrict the number of people in the library.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Reconfigure interiors and design public areas to maintain the physical distancing requirement for staff and visitors. 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Removing chairs and tables
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Manage the flow of people by implementing one-way walkways 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Provide hand sanitizing stations at all facility entryways for everyone to use.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') A barrier is set in the checkout area. 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Post COVID-19 protocols throughout the library.
                        
                        li.pb-15
                            div Cleaning Protocols
                            div The administrators should ensure disinfection is an important part of maintaining a safe environment. 
                            ul
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') 
                                    span Cleaning and disinfect procedures should be done according to this link 
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/CleaningDisinfecting_PublicSettings.pdf" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/CleaningDisinfecting_PublicSettings.pdf
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Make sure we have enough handwashing facilities on site for all our staff and students. Handwashing locations are easily accessed.  Extra hand sanitizers are put in the entrance, in the entrance of the library and in the entrance of the 2nd floor. 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Staff must wash their hands regularly throughout the day and practice good hygiene all time. 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') The administrators who are cleaning and disinfecting have adequate training and materials to do so.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Make sure all unnecessary tools and equipment are removed — e.g., coffee makers and shared utensils and plates.
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') The administrative team disinfects the all identified common areas and shared tools including washrooms, tools, equipment, shared tables, desks, light switches, and door handles:
                                ul
                                    li.ml-15(style='list-style:lower-roman') Before and at the end of a “work at the office day”.
                                    li.ml-15(style='list-style:lower-roman') Before and after someone is using an area, i.e. onsite class.
                                    li.ml-15(style='list-style:lower-roman') Periodically throughout the day, especially during the “open to the public” hours
                                    li.ml-15(style='list-style:lower-roman') At the end of the day 
                                li(style='list-style:decimal') Staff are asked to wipe the tables after where they finished their meals.

                        li.pb-15(style="overflow: hidden")
                            div Resources 
                            ul
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span COVID-19 Go-Forward Guidelines for B.C.’s Post-Secondary Sector (
                                    a(href="https://www2.gov.bc.ca/assets/gov/education/post-secondary-education/institution-resources-administration/aest_postsecgoforwardguidelines.pdf?bcgovtm=20200506_GCPE_AM_COVID_9_NOTIFICATION_BCGOV_BCGOV_EN_BC__NOTIFICATION" target="_blank") https://www2.gov.bc.ca/assets/gov/education/post-secondary-education/institution-resources-administration/aest_postsecgoforwardguidelines.pdf?bcgovtm=20200506_GCPE_AM_COVID_9_NOTIFICATION_BCGOV_BCGOV_EN_BC__NOTIFICATION
                                    span )
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span BC COVID-19 self-assessment tool (
                                    a(href="https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en" target="_blank") https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en
                                    span )
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span COVID-19 Testing: 
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/testing" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/testing
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span Understand contact tracing: 
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation/contact-tracing" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation/contact-tracing
                                li(style='list-style:decimal')
                                    span COVID-19 Care: 
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/about-covid-19/if-you-are-sick" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/about-covid-19/if-you-are-sick
