                section#robust-case-management
                    h3 CCST Vancouver’s Plan for robust case management
                    div All staff and students are required to contact the CCST Vancouver office if they are tested positive to COVID-19 or develop symptoms during a school term, although most of our courses and activities are hosted online.
                    div The administrative team commits to collaborate, share information, and review emergency plans with their local PHO whenever necessary.  
                    ul
                        li.pb-15
                            div Immediate Communication with the PHO and the CCST Community 
                            div If a staff or student is tested positive to COVID-19

                        li.pb-15
                            div The administrator will contact the health authority as soon as possible to report a confirmed case in the CCST Vancouver community.
                            ul.pb-15
                                li The administrator will contact the CCST Vancouver community.
                                li The person who is sick will be asked to self-isolate at home for 14 days and follow the quarantine and isolation policies.
                                li The administrator will ask all staff and students to be prepared for the following up steps taken by the PHO.  
                                li The Registrar Office will assist the contact tracing process using our school data base system.
                                li We understand that only those who are considered “close contacts” will be asked by public health officials to self-isolate and monitor for COVID-19 symptoms for 14 days. But we will send a general communication to the community of CCST Vancouver to bring the exposure to their attention.
                                li The administrator will follow the guideline provided by the PHO to disinfect the campus.  We will arrange professional team to do so when necessary
                                li The administrator will assign a staff to contact the person who is sick every day during the quarantine period and make sure his/her medical and daily needs are taken care of. 

                        li.pb-15
                            div Involve a Response Team 
                            div The administrative team is the response team for any outbreak or other significant COVID-19-related event. Following are their responsibilities:
                            ul
                                li Support contact tracing efforts by exploring options for students/faculty/staff to track their activities/contact/movement (e.g., contact tracing apps)
                                li Provide updated COVID-19 information for people who are isolating.
                                li Connect people who are isolating with the Dean of Students to take care of their emotional and spiritual needs.
                                li Develop policy encouraging flexibility for personal circumstances, including flexible attendance and sick-leave policies.
                                li 
                                    span Ensure that students/faculty/staff are aware of financial and other support programs available to those with financial instability related to COVID-19.&nbsp;
                                    a(href='https://www.canada.ca/en/department-finance/economic-response-plan.html' target='_blank') https://www.canada.ca/en/department-finance/economic-response-plan.html

                        li.pb-15
                            div Monitoring, screening and testing for COVID-19 
                            ul
                                li During the pandemic, the CCST Vancouver Community is encouraged to monitor their health daily for symptoms of COVID-19 and get tested if they develop symptoms compatible with COVID-19.
                                li 
                                    span Students are encouraged to monitor their own health and self-isolate themselves if experiencing illness. They can do it via the self-assessment tool.&nbsp;
                                    a(href="https://bc.thrive.health/ " target="_blank") https://bc.thrive.health/ 
                                li 
                                    span In case students/faculty/staff needed to be connected with the testing facilities, they can find a collection center near them from the link below.&nbsp;
                                    a(href="https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/3862560c5a41418e9d78f4f81688e9d0 " target="_blank") https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/3862560c5a41418e9d78f4f81688e9d0 

                        li.pb-15
                            div Case management of a student/faculty or staff member in the event of an outbreak
                            div Scenario 1: If a staff or student is tested positive to COVID-19
                            ul
                                li The administrator will contact the health authority as soon as possible to report a confirmed case in the CCST Vancouver community.
                                li The administrator will contact the CCST Vancouver community and communicate with them.
                                li The whole community must self-isolate at home whether one has symptoms or not, or as directed by the local public health authority.
                                li The whole community must self-isolate at home whether one has symptoms or not, or as directed by the local public health authority.
                                li The administrator will ask all staff and students to be prepared for the following up steps taken by the PHO.  The community of CCST Vancouver should do their best to assist the procedure of the contact tracing. 
                                li We understand that only those who are considered “close contacts” will be asked by public health officials to self-isolate and monitor for COVID-19 symptoms for 14 days. But we will send a general communication to the community of CCST Vancouver to bring the outbreak to their attention.
                                li The administrator will follow the guideline provided by the PHO to disinfect the campus.  We will arrange professional team to do so when necessary.

                            div(style="padding-top:15px") Scenario 2: If a staff or student shows symptoms of COVID-19
                            div If a faculty, staff or student develop symptoms while at the institution, we will follow the following protocols:
                            ul
                                li Separate the symptomatic individual from others in a supervised area and direct the symptomatic individual to return to his/her place of residence. Arrangement for transportation should be coordinated if required. 
                                li If symptoms persist, the individual should be instructed to contact 8-1-1 or his/her local healthcare provider for further direction. 
                                li Staff responsible for facility cleaning must clean and disinfect the space where the individual is separated and any areas that have been used by them (e.g., classroom, bathroom, common areas) immediately.
                                li The administrator will contact the PHO to report the incident and seek for further instruction.
                                li The administrator will follow the guideline provided by the PHO to disinfect the campus.  We will arrange professional team to do so when necessary.

                            div(style="padding-top:15px") Scenario 3: If faculty, staff or students develop symptoms at home or potentially exposed to COVID-19
                            ul
                                li The person will be asked to self-isolate at home and monitor the symptoms for 14 days.
                                li If the person develops during the isolation, he/she must restart the isolation time directed by the local public health authority.
                                li If the symptoms persist, the individual should be instructed to contact 8-1-1 or his/her local healthcare provider for further direction.  
                                li If the person is tested positive to COVID-19, we will follow the procedure in scenario 1.

                            div(style="padding-top:15px") Scenario 4: A staff or student is recovered from COVID-19
                            ul
                                li 
                                    div We promote a reliable and accurate message about COVID-19 to the community of the CCST Vancouver during the pandemic.
                                    div 
                                        span Reference: BC Center for Disease Control&nbsp;
                                        a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/COVID-19" target="_target") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/COVID-19 
                                        span &nbsp;and minimize social stigma associated with COVID-19.
                                li The staff team will communicate with the community of the CCST Vancouver and request every one of us to protect the confidentiality of each staff and student during and after one’s sickness. We will use our email communication and online chapel time speaking out against negative behaviors toward those who may experience stigma. 
                        
                        li.pb-15
                            div Contact tracing
                            ul
                                li The Registrar Office will assist the contact tracing process via our school system. 
                                li The Administration Office will provide the daily sign-in sheet to determine the possible close contact of a sick person.
                                li When necessary, the administrative team will provide the record in the on-campus video cameras to determine who the possible close contact of a sick person is.
                                li 
                                    span The administrative team should understand the contact tracing procedure.&nbsp;
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation/contact-tracing" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation/contact-tracing

                        li.pb-15
                            div Quarantine and isolation policies
                            ul
                                li The following people must follow the quarantine and isolation policies: a student/faculty or staff member are positive in a COVID-19 test, a student/faculty or staff member who has travelled oversea in the past 14 days, and a student/faculty or staff member who are instructed by the providential health officer. 
                                li 
                                    div During the quarantine, an individual must follow the instructions from the BCCDC’s DOs and Don’ts of self-isolation.
                                    div
                                        a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/Self-isolation_dos_donts.pdf" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/Health-Info-Site/Documents/Self-isolation_dos_donts.pdf


                                                    
                        

                section#international-students
                    h3 COVID-19 Safety Plan for International Students
                    ul
                        li.pb-15
                            div Overall Communication
                            ul
                                li The general COVID-19 safety plan is put on the website for all students and applicants for reference.
                                li Public links from the health authorities regarding the updated changes in B.C. are put on the website under the COVID-19 Safety Plan.  International students should check regularly prior to their departure.
                                li 
                                    div International students should read carefully about studying in Canada during pandemic
                                    div
                                        a(href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/coronavirus-covid19/students.html" target="_blank") https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/coronavirus-covid19/students.html 
                                li 
                                    span All international students should understand the Quarantine Act. As of March 25, 2020 it is mandatory, under the Quarantine Act (
                                    a(href="https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/news/2020/03/new-order-makes-self-isolation-mandatory-for-individuals-entering-canada.html" target="_blank") https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/news/2020/03/new-order-makes-self-isolation-mandatory-for-individuals-entering-canada.html
                                    span ) that anyone arriving in British Columbia from outside of Canada to self-isolate and monitor for symptoms for 14 days upon their arrival and complete the federal ArriveCAN application (
                                    a(href="https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/safety/emergency-preparedness-response-recovery/covid-19-provincial-support/self-isolation-on-return" target="_blank") https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/safety/emergency-preparedness-response-recovery/covid-19-provincial-support/self-isolation-on-return
                                    span ). Learn more about self-isolation at this dedicated page (
                                    a(href="http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation" target="_blank") http://www.bccdc.ca/health-info/diseases-conditions/covid-19/self-isolation
                                    span ).

                        li.pb-15
                            div Pre-Arrival Communication – Study in Canada during Pandemic
                            ul
                                li 
                                    span All international students must share the content with their co-arriving family members regarding the COVID-19 situation in Canada&nbsp;
                                    a(href="http://www.covid-19canada.com/" target="_blank") http://www.covid-19canada.com/ 
                                    span &nbsp;and the COVID-19 Safety Plan at CCST Vancouver.
                                li All international students are required to download Government of Canada’s ArriveCAN application prior to arrival at the border and complete the information required.
                                li 
                                    span All international students must understand the mandatory 14-day quarantine and all quarantine requirements.&nbsp;
                                    a(href="https://orders-in-council.canada.ca/attachment.php?attach=39613&lang=en" target="_blank") https://orders-in-council.canada.ca/attachment.php?attach=39613&lang=en
                                li 
                                    span All international students must get ready the BC COVID-19 Self-Assessment Tool in their devices&nbsp;
                                    a(href="https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en" target="_blank") https://bc.thrive.health/covid19/en
                                li All international students should arrange to arrive the quarantine location NOT by public transit.  CCST Vancouver will pre-arrange a volunteer to pick up the arriving students and their co-arriving family members to the quarantine location when necessary. All volunteers will be briefed about all the necessary safety procedure, i.e. wear a mask, disinfect the car before and after, keep a physical distancing whenever possible.
                                li 
                                    div Either the students choose to quarantine in a serviced hotel or a private home, the quarantine location should NOT be:
                                    ul
                                        li(style='list-style:lower-roman') a group or communal living setting, including camps or students dorms unless the location is pre-authorized;
                                        li(style='list-style:lower-roman') a household with a large family or many people
                                        li(style='list-style:lower-roman') a shared small apartment or similar setting
                                li CCST Vancouver will do our best to assist the international students to prepare the quarantine location prior the arrival of them.
                            
                        li.pb-15
                            div 14-day Quarantine Requirements
                            ul
                                li CCST Vancouver will ask the international students and the co-arriving family members to do daily self-check by using BC COVID-19 Self-Assessment Tool.
                                li International students must register with the ArriveCAN to submit their travel and contact information, quarantine plan and the COVID-19 symptom self-assessments before they board their flight to Canada.  And they must access the apps daily during the 14-day quarantine period or as instructed by the PHO.
                                li Our staff will communicate and confirm with the international students and their family members and make sure they are symptom free.  If any symptom develops during the quarantine period, we will follow the procedure in the CCST Vancouver’s Plan for robust case management.
                                li We will assign a staff to call and communicate with the student who is in a quarantine situation.  We will make sure the student’s daily needs are met either by providing supplies to them directly or provide information for the student to reach other local contactless grocery services or medical services.  
                                li Our Dean of Students will be in touch regularly with the international students who are in a quarantine situation and offer spiritual and emotional support. 
                                li CCST Vancouver takes the violations of the Quarantine Act seriously.  Specific information will be gathered and recorded and report to local authorities as soon as we find out a noncompliance situation.  
                            
                        li.pb-15
                            div Post-quarantine Requirements
                            ul
                                li The CCST Vancouver Community will continue to support international students and immediate family members after completion of their 14-day quarantine period.
                                li The CCST Vancouver office will connect the individuals to the Student councils and the staff team, and provide all local resources through the International Student Guide.




